==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-wail.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''wail'''
# A loud [[cry]] or [[shriek]].
#:''She let out a loud, doleful '''wail'''.''

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|wail||}}

# To [[cry]] out, as in sorrow.
# To [[weep]] loudly.
# To make a noise like crying.
#:''The wind '''wailed''' and the rain streamed down.''

